# =============================================================================
# Bashmenu External Scripts Configuration
# =============================================================================
# This file defines external scripts that will appear in the Bashmenu menu.
# Scripts are loaded automatically when Bashmenu starts.
#
# Format: Display Name|Absolute Path|Description|Required Level|Parameters
#
# Fields:
#   1. Display Name    - Text shown in the menu (max 50 characters)
#   2. Absolute Path   - Full path to the script (must be executable)
#   3. Description     - Brief description of what the script does (max 100 chars)
#   4. Required Level  - Permission level: 1=user, 2=admin, 3=root
#   5. Parameters      - Optional default parameters to pass to the script
#
# Rules:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments and will be ignored
#   - Empty lines are ignored
#   - Scripts must have execute permissions (chmod +x script.sh)
#   - Scripts must be in allowed directories (see ALLOWED_SCRIPT_DIRS in config.conf)
#   - Use absolute paths only (e.g., /opt/bashmenu/plugins/myscript.sh)
#
# Security:
#   - Scripts are validated before execution
#   - Parameters are sanitized to prevent command injection
#   - Scripts outside ALLOWED_SCRIPT_DIRS will be blocked
#
# =============================================================================

